"The palate opens with a touch of earth, a mild saltiness and a brightening coriander note. A touch of earthy funk is also present. As with the base beer, the salt levels are low, but completely appropriate and extremely refreshing. Light in body with a drying, snappy finish, maybe a touch watery?  Carbonation is crisp. Awesome stuff."
